(43, 11, 43, 42, 7, 14, 15, NULL, 'Resurrection of the Dead', 'Both passages emphasize the command to arise from death. In John, Jesus calls Lazarus to come forth, while in Luke, Jesus tells the young man to arise, resulting in both being restored to life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 43, 41, 4, 41, 41, NULL, 'Authority Over Life and Nature', 'This connection highlights the authority of Jesus over both life and nature. In John 11:43, Jesus commands Lazarus to come forth, demonstrating his power over death, while in Mark 4:41, the disciples marvel at his ability to command the wind and sea, showing his dominion over creation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 43, 5, 25, 25, NULL, 'Resurrection and Life Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as both passages discuss the dead responding to the voice of Jesus. In John 11:44, Lazarus is raised from the dead, while John 5:25 speaks of the dead hearing His voice and living.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 43, 20, 7, 7, 'with graveclothes: and his face was bound about with a napkin', 'Connection of Graveclothes and Napkin', 'This connection highlights the presence of graveclothes and a napkin in both passages. In John 11:44, the dead man is described as being bound with graveclothes, while John 20:7 specifically mentions the napkin about Jesus'' head, emphasizing the significance of these burial wrappings.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 42, 7, 15, 15, 'he that was dead', 'Resurrection and Restoration', 'Both passages emphasize the act of raising the dead, showcasing Jesus'' authority over death. In John, Lazarus comes forth bound, while in Luke, the young man sits up and speaks, indicating restoration to life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 50, 3, 21, 21, 'he that was dead came forth', 'Transformation of the Body', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation from death to life. In John 11:44, Lazarus is raised from the dead, while Philippians 3:21 speaks of changing our vile body to a glorious one, emphasizing the power of resurrection.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 1, 1, 3, 3, NULL, 'Light and Life Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation from death to life. In John 11:44, the act of Jesus calling Lazarus forth parallels God''s command in Genesis 1:3, where light emerges from darkness, symbolizing new beginnings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 9, 2, 6, 6, NULL, 'Resurrection and Divine Power', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of life and death, highlighting God''s authority to bring individuals back to life. John 11:44 illustrates Jesus'' power to resurrect Lazarus, while 1 Samuel 2:6 states that the Lord brings people up from the grave.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 44, 44, 20, 9, 12, NULL, 'Resurrection and Restoration', 'This connection highlights the theme of resurrection, as both passages describe individuals who were dead and then brought back to life. In John 11:44, Lazarus is called forth from the grave, while in Acts 20:9-12, Eutychus is restored to life after falling. Both instances emphasize the power of God to restore life.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 45, 43, 2, 23, 23, 'believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus through Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Jesus resulting from witnessing miracles. In John 11:45, many believed after seeing what Jesus did, paralleling John 2:23 where belief arose from observing his miracles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 45, 43, 11, 19, 19, 'many of the Jews', 'Connection of Belief and Comfort', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of many Jews who came to support Martha and Mary, and later, those who believed in Jesus after witnessing his actions. This connection highlights the communal aspect of grief and faith in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
