(43, 11, 45, 43, 12, 9, 11, 'believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus and Lazarus', 'Both passages emphasize the belief of many Jews in Jesus due to the miraculous raising of Lazarus. The SOURCE verse notes that many believed on him after witnessing his works, while the TARGET passage shows that many came to see Lazarus, leading to further belief in Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 45, 43, 12, 17, 19, 'believed on him', 'Belief in Jesus'' Miracles', 'This connection highlights how the belief of many Jews in Jesus, as noted in John 11:45, is reinforced in John 12:17-19, where those who witnessed Lazarus'' resurrection bear record of this miracle. Both passages emphasize the impact of Jesus'' miraculous acts on the people''s faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 46, 43, 9, 13, 13, 'the Pharisees', 'Connection to the Pharisees', 'This connection highlights the involvement of the Pharisees in both narratives. In John 11:46, individuals report Jesus'' actions to the Pharisees, while in John 9:13, a man healed by Jesus is brought to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 46, 42, 16, 30, 31, 'what things Jesus had done', 'Response to Jesus'' Miracles', 'This connection highlights the theme of disbelief despite miraculous signs. In John, the Pharisees hear of Jesus'' deeds but do not believe, paralleling the idea in Luke that even if someone rises from the dead, they may not be persuaded.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 11, 46, 43, 5, 15, 16, 'told them what things Jesus had done', 'Persecution of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the response of the Jews to Jesus'' actions. In John 11:46, some went to inform the Pharisees about Jesus, while in John 5:15-16, the man tells the Jews about Jesus healing him, leading to persecution.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
